Description: The premier social network connecting musicians, producers, and engineers.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Just finished cutting a new recording and need to find the right person to make it promotable? The hard work of writing your songs and bringing the right band mates or harmonies together to make them sound as they appeared in your mind might be all for naught if you have yet to connect with a reliable producer. TuneOrg might just be the instrument to create that link. A new social network designed to connect music artists with producers and recording engineers, TuneOrg allows users to create profiles as either an artist or producer detailing information such as online presence and music background. Profiles can be viewed by both members and non-members of TuneOrg and contain links to biography information, skills, photos, web links, and music. Connections play a key role in breaking into the music scene and TuneOrg aims to kick-start musical projects that can launch careers in the industry. The founders of TuneOrg envision a platform to provide as much help to individuals committed to making a living in a challenging music industry. “We created this site in the hopes that it will help musicians, producers, and engineers of all levels network with each other to further their careers in the industry,” says founder Landon Ouyang. “Behind all popular and great music there is a team. With TuneOrg, you will be able to put together your team to make your music dreams come true.” Along with standard social network features – status updates, uploading photos, sharing links – users can also upload songs, create blog postings and search for collaborators based on instruments played, skillset and location. Users can additionally participate in discussion forums related to the music industry and post or respond to job requests in an online jobs board. The site is free to join.
Industry Groups: Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio

Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: We are looking to purchase a radio station or group of stations with sellers who are in a position to owner finance the sale, preferably in a top 150 broadcasting market & in Florida. Our partnership, with combined experience of over 50 years, marries a radio operations/program specialist with a sales & business development specialist.  Todd has worked with small independent & large corporate Radio stations, as well as TV broadcasting & video for 25 years.  Dave has experience selling to Fortune 1000 companies as well as “Mom and Pops”, as well as building sales teams & long-term profitable relationships for 25+ years. This combined experience sets us apart from the average & with the help of owner financing we will successfully build & grow the advertising base, increasing revenues & paying off the debt aggressively.   Due to our limited capital & credit, we would like to make a handsome offer for a company as an incentive to sell their business to us.  We are very open-minded to creative financing & looking for a win-win agreement.  We have found some great opportunities so far but we lack the capital to get started in the form of a 10-20% down payment & operating capital while we establish &/or grow the station based upon the needs of the market. We estimate our capital needs at $250K to 2 Million, based upon the asking price of the station, etc.  We are seeking capital for either the down  payment with owner financing or full purchase, along with operating expenses for approximately 1-2 years.  What we are offering in return is full capital payback with a partial business lifetime equity stake or a negotiated full partner business lifetime equity stake. If this is of serious interest to you, please contact us at 813-803-2203 or by email at ttdcommunications@gmail.com and we’ll be glad to discuss this opportunity further. Thank you kindly for your consideration.  We look forward to hearing from you soon. Have a great day! Todd & Dave TTD
